{
  "slide": 7,
  "duration": 77.74,
  "text": "Now let's talk about the cleaning verification module, which is a module that is at the core of this digital platform. What it does in essence is to transform the master cleaning schedule that you agree with your clients in the SLAs. It takes an entire area looking at what needs to be cleaned in that area, and then transforming that into a digital task. Now what you put in that digital task is entirely up to you, but that's then what is available to the guys on site. It typically addresses the what, the when, the how, the who, specs, corrective actions, even if you want to take it to a level where you attach standards as photographs to say, this is what a clean mixer looks like. These digital tasks are then attached to some form of proof of presence at the site, where you can use things like QR accords, bar accords, NFC tags, RFID tags. And this would demand that the guys on site activate a proof of presence that shows indeed I was in this area and was able to sign off these digital tasks that speak to our SLA.",
